# Learning to add files to the repository

## mkdir
	make a new folder

## git status
	give the status of the changes in the repository
## add
	use -touch- to create a file (.css, .js, .html)
		touch index.html
		touch index.js
		touch main.css
	git add index.html  	#<- this add the file to te staging area
	git rm --cached index.html 	#<- this remove the file from the stagind area
	git add . 	#<- this add all the files from this ("learning-git" in this case) current directory downwards
	git rm -r --cached . 	#<- this remove all the files from the staging area
	
## git commit
	is a save point before start implementing new features
	git commit -m "bootstrap project"	 #<- the message has to be descritive
	
## vi
	you vizualize the file and you can edit it

## git diff
	shows the diference/chenges in the file
	
## git restore <file>
	discard the changes
		
	
